ely.\n\nHere\u0027s the F# code to achieve this:\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060fsharp\nlet rec factorial n =\n    if n \u003C 0 then\n        \u0022Error: Negative input\u0022\n    elif n = 0 then\n        1\n    else\n        n * factorial (n - 1)\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\nThis function uses recursion to calculate the factorial of a number. It includes an edge case check for negative inputs, returning an error message if the input is negative.\n\n### Inform\n\nThe F# function to calculate the factorial of a number using recursion and handle edge cases for 0 and negative numbers is:\n\n\u0060\u0060\u0060fsharp\nlet rec factorial n =\n    if n \u003C 0 then\n        \u0022Error: Negative input\u0022\n    elif n = 0 then\n        1\n    else\n        n * factorial (n - 1)\n\u0060\u0060\u0060\n\nThis function will correctly calculate the factorial for non-negative integers and return an error message for negative inputs.\u0022\n     Timestamp = 2025-12-28 8:44:49 AM\n     Metadata = map [] }]",
